# Project conventions

## Extension (tiktok-hook-analyzer)

- Vanilla JS only — no React, no build step, no npm packages
- All analysis logic lives in `analysis-core.js` (THA object)
- API keys always read from `chrome.storage.sync` at call time — never hardcoded
- Funnel classification always uses `THA.formatFunnelClassificationBlock()` — never write raw funnel category strings
- Save buttons fire only on explicit user click — no automatic analysis
- UI colours: `#0a0a0a` background, `#fe2c55` accent, white text
- New UI elements need a corresponding entry in `els` object at top of `sidepanel.js`

## Hub (tiktok-intelligence-hub)

- All IPC channels named `hub:*` and handled in `electron/main.ts`
- New IPC channels must be exposed in `electron/preload.ts` and typed in `src/hub.d.ts`
- Database access via `JsonStore` only — never read/write database JSON files directly
- Product research (`productResearch.ts`) is one-time per product — check `research_completed_at` before calling
- Agent memory sync is silent (no `sendAgentMessage`) — use `flushPending` in `agentBridge.ts` only
- Scripts and daily plans pass `additionalInfo` from the UI through to the prompt context
- ElevenLabs audio files named `ScriptTitle_YYYY-MM-DD.mp3` — never use UUIDs as filenames
- Personal library imports (`personal_library.json`) go to `my_videos` table, never `library_items`
- `pending_hub_review` is cleared when user edits + saves a My Videos entry

## Whisper server

- Python Flask, port 5050, shared by extension and hub
- Never change port without updating both `analysis-core.js` and hub sync service
- Video downloads are always to a temp directory, cleaned up after use

## Compliance (non-negotiable)

- Never suggest health claims or bodily effect descriptions for WildGut or Careleaf products
- CTA must always end with: "I don't know how long this deal is gonna last but I've left the link in the yellow basket below."
- Read `/hub/compliance.md` (or `COMPLIANCE_RULES` in `hubContextSnapshot.ts`) before writing any script content

## Git / data

- `settings.json` is always gitignored — never commit it
- Run `npm run data:export` before committing hub changes that affect library/products/sales
- `whisper-server/cookies.txt` is always gitignored
